title: Atomic Cafe (1982) - documentary
description:
THE ATOMIC CAFE (1982)
Documentary

Newsreel, government and military films and other historic media including phonograph records are used to depict the social climate of the United States during the Cold War (1946-1962 roughly).

Informative, humorous, a genuine work of art to be viewed repeatedly unlike many documentaries.

MPEG-4 Nero Digital file recoded from US NTSC DVD rip.
Resolution 704x480
Frame rate 29.97
Audio: AAC-HE (mono)

Looks and sounds really good.
